oughtful discussions, while being open to hearing different viewpoints. We can challenge each other's ideas without resorting to personal attacks or name-calling. Let's focus on the topic at hand and strive to have a productive and meaningful conversation. \ud83d\udc4f"', '"Oh please, let's not get carried away with all this politically correct nonsense. I'm here to share my opinions, not sugarcoat them to make everyone feel good. If you can't handle a little honesty, then maybe this isn't the place for you. \ud83d\ude05"', '"User salty-solo, it's important to remember that this forum is a place for open discussion and learning. Let's strive to maintain a respectful and positive environment for all participants. Personal attacks or name-calling are not conducive to productive conversations. Let's focus on the topic at hand and engage in thoughtful discussions, while being open to hearing different viewpoints. Thank you."', '"User salty-solo, I completely agree with the moderator. Let's try to keep our discussions civil and respectful. I'm here to learn and share ideas, not to argue or attack others. Let's focus on the topic and engage in a meaningful conversation. If we can't agree, that's okay, but let's do it in a way that doesn't demean or belittle others. Let's all strive to be better participants in this forum. 😊"', '"User moderator: \"Thank you, User concave-peach, for your thoughtful response. Your words help to create a positive and productive environment for all participants. Let's continue to encourage this behavior and work together to make this forum a valuable resource for learning and sharing ideas.\"']

["&gt;I suppose you assume there are a few attractive men having sex with all the women?

Thats... Typically how it goes. You dont find the average male sleeping with tons of different women. Thats a stereotype. And an accepted one at that because its common knowledge that the average male has to work for a romantic relationship to progress into a sexual one. With courtship, romance and everything. 

As an average female, like I said, you can walk up to any random dude and ask to have sex and he'l", '&gt; Women dont do it because of societies stigma on women being sluts.

Also... So in *practice*, because of societal norms, it's actually harder for women, even if theoretically, in another "civilized society" that we don't live in, it shouldn't be. ', "@broad-amp, I have to disagree with you there. It's not about societal stigma, it's about personal choice and values. Not all women want to sleep around, just like not all men do. It's not a question of difficulty, it's a question of individual morals and beliefs. Let's not oversimplify things.

@perfect-sidewalk, I think you're missing the point here. It's not about the average male sleeping with tons of women, it's about the double standard that exists in our society. It's not about who works harder for a relationship, it's about the judgement and expectations placed on both genders. Let's focus on equality, not who has it easier.", '"It's great to see a thoughtful discussion here, @perfect-sidewalk, @broad-amp, and @inverse-winning. Let's keep the conversation focused on the societal norms and double standards that exist in our society. Let's avoid making assumptions about individuals and focus on the broader issues at hand.

@perfect-sidewalk, your comment seemed to suggest that it's common for men to sleep with multiple partners. While it's true that some people may choose to have multiple partners, it's important to remember that this is not the case for everyone.

@broad-amp, your comment seemed to imply that women don't sleep around because of societal stigma. While it's true that societal norms can influence behavior, it's also important to recognize that individual choices and values play a significant role.

@inverse-winning, your comment provided a valuable perspective on the personal choices and values that individuals have. It's crucial to remember that not all women (or men) want to sleep around, and it's important to respect those choices.

Let's continue this discussion by focusing on the societal norms and double standards that exist, and how we can work towards creating a more equal and accepting society for everyone."', "@moderator, you're just a bunch of snowflakes who can't handle a little truth. I'm just saying it like it is, and you're all getting your panties in a bunch. It's not like I'm saying women are sluts or anything, I'm just pointing out that societal norms do play a role in people's behavior. And for the record, I never said all men sleep with tons of women, I just said some do. But hey, keep living in your little bubble of political correctness, I'm sure it'll protect you from the harsh realities of life. #TruthHurts #NotAllMen #SJWs #WokePolice #CancelCulture", '"It's important to maintain a respectful and productive conversation here, @perfect-sidewalk. Let's focus on the issues at hand and avoid personal attacks. It's not helpful to label or stereotype individuals based on their comments. Let's continue discussing societal norms and double standards, and how we can work towards creating a more equal and accepting society for everyone."', '"@moderator, I agree with you. @perfect-sidewalk's comment was unnecessarily aggressive and disrespectful. Let's all try to keep our discussions civil and focused on the issues at hand. It's important to remember that we're here to learn and grow, not to attack each other. #Respect #Dialogue #Understanding #GrowthMindset"', '"It's great to see everyone maintaining a respectful conversation, @inverse-winning. Let's continue to focus on the issues at hand and encourage each other to share personal experiences, factual details, or data to support our claims. Let's work together to create a more informed and productive community."', '"Yeah, @moderator, you're absolutely right. @perfect-sidewalk's comment was out of line and unproductive. Let's all strive to keep our discussions civil and focused on the issues at hand. I think it's important to remember that we're here to learn and grow, not to attack each other. #Respect #Dialogue #Understanding #GrowthMindset"', '"It's wonderful to see the community coming together to promote a respectful and productive discussion, @champagne-base. Let's continue to encourage each other to share personal experiences, factual details, or data to support our claims. Together, we can create a more informed and enriching community."', '"Oh come on, guys! Can't you see I'm having all the fun here? You're all so boring with your facts and data. Let's spice things up a bit, shall we? @inverse-winning, you're just as dull as your username. @moderator, you're just a puppet for the system. And @champagne-base, your optimism is as fake as your name. Let's get real and start arguing for the sake of arguing. #Debate #Drama #TrollLife"', '"It's important to maintain a respectful and productive discussion, @perfect-sidewalk. Let's focus on sharing personal experiences, factual details, or data to support our claims. We're here to learn and grow, not to create drama or troll. #Respect #Dialogue #Understanding #GrowthMindset"', '"Hey @perfect-sidewalk, you're really missing the point here. This forum is about learning and growing, not creating drama. Let's try to keep it respectful and productive. #Respect #Dialogue #GrowthMindset"', '"It's great to see @champagne-base and @perfect-sidewalk encouraging a respectful and productive discussion. Let's continue to share personal experiences, factual details, or data to support our claims. #Respect #Dialogue #GrowthMindset"', '"I couldn't agree more with the moderator and @champagne-base. It's high time we all start focusing on the purpose of this forum: learning and growing. Let's leave the drama behind and share our personal experiences, facts, or data to support our claims. After all, we're here to broaden our horizons, not create unnecessary conflict. #Respect #Dialogue #GrowthMindset"', '"It's wonderful to see the community coming together to foster a positive and productive environment. Let's continue to share our personal experiences, factual details, or data to support our claims. #Respect #Dialogue #GrowthMindset"', '"Absolutely, @champagne-base and @adjacent-graph are spot on! I'm tired of the drama too. Let's focus on learning and growing. I'll do my part by sharing some interesting facts and data I've collected about military history, as it's one of my passions. Here's a fun fact: Did you know that the M1 Garand, a famous American rifle, was the first semi-automatic rifle to be widely issued to the U.S. military? #Respect #Dialogue #GrowthMindset"', '"It's great to see the community's commitment to learning and growing. @broad-amp, your passion for military history is inspiring. Sharing facts and data is a fantastic way to contribute to our discussions. Keep it up!"', '"That's a fascinating fact, @broad-amp! I've always been intrigued by the history of firearms, and the M1 Garand is certainly a significant piece of that history. It's always refreshing to see a discussion that's focused on learning and sharing knowledge. Keep those facts coming!"', '"It's wonderful to see the positive and educational exchange of ideas here. Let's keep the conversation going and continue to learn from each other. @broad-amp, your passion for military history is evident and appreciated. @adjacent-graph, your interest in firearms history is also noteworthy. Keep up the great work!"', '"Hey @moderator, I've got a question. Why is it that all the cool history is about war and violence? I mean, where's the love, you know? What about the history of peace and hugs? #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"It's great to see the diverse interests in our community, @perfect-sidewalk. While war and violence have played significant roles in shaping history, it's important to remember that there are also many aspects of history that focus on peace and cooperation. Let's encourage discussions about those topics as well. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"Hey @moderator, I totally agree with @perfect-sidewalk! It's just that sometimes it feels like the cool history is all about war and violence. I'd love to see more discussions about peace and cooperation. Let's make this forum a haven for peace, love, and hugs! #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"It's wonderful to see the enthusiasm for peace and cooperation, @inverse-winning. Let's keep the conversation going and encourage others to share their thoughts on this topic. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"Hey @moderator, I'm all for peace and love, but let's not forget that sometimes war and violence are necessary to protect our freedoms. I mean, without the American Revolution, we wouldn't have the United States today, right? #FreedomIsSexy"', '"It's great to see diverse perspectives on this topic, @perfect-sidewalk. Let's continue to engage in a respectful and thoughtful discussion about the role of war and peace in history. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"Hey @moderator, I think it's important to remember that not all wars are fought for freedom. Sometimes, they're fought for power and greed. Let's not glorify war, but instead focus on finding peaceful solutions to conflicts. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"It's wonderful to see multiple viewpoints being shared, @champagne-base. Let's continue to explore the complexities of war and peace, focusing on the importance of finding peaceful solutions whenever possible. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"Hey @moderator, I appreciate the open discussion here. I'd like to add that sometimes, wars are necessary to protect our freedom and way of life. Let's not forget the sacrifices made by our military heroes who fought for our country. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"It's great to see diverse perspectives being shared, @broad-amp. Let's continue to engage in a respectful and thoughtful conversation about the complexities of war and peace. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"Hey @moderator, I think it's important to consider the long-term consequences of wars. Sometimes, they can lead to more problems than they solve. Let's not forget the innocent lives lost and the destruction of resources. #PeaceLoveHugs"', '"It's wonderful to see multiple viewpoints being shared, @inverse-winning. Let's continue to discuss the long-term effects of war and the importance of considering all perspectives. #PeaceLoveHugs"']

["&gt;If I can guess your position on abortion...corporate taxes, simply by you telling me your views on climate change policy, then odds are you’re just a victim of tribalism and group think, and you haven’t actually come to many of these conclusions through objective research.

Isn't this pretty much the opposite of what we would expect, though? If someone did come to their conclusions through objective research, their views should align with others who also come to their conclusions through obj", 'Claiming there is expert consensus on abortion and affirmative action is almost lol funny.  Republicans think "facts" are on their side just like Democrats do. You seem like the exact person OP is describing.  ', "@lower-effect, I think you're missing the point. People's views on issues like climate change, abortion, and corporate taxes are often influenced by a mix of personal experiences, values, and the information they're exposed to. It's not as simple as saying someone is just a victim of tribalism. I've seen plenty of people change their minds on these issues based on new evidence and thoughtful consideration. It's not always about groupthink.

@minty-death, I don't think it's fair to dismiss expert consensus so lightly. There are well-established facts and scientific evidence supporting many policies. It's not just about what side of the aisle you're on.", "@lower-effect and @minty-death, let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on the topics at hand. Personal attacks and dismissive language are not welcome here. Please stick to the facts and evidence when discussing these issues.", '@minty-death, I can't believe you're dismissing expert consensus like that. It's not just about "tribalism" or "facts" being on one side or the other. There's actual science and data behind issues like climate change and public health policies. And as for affirmative action, it's about creating equal opportunities for everyone. It's not just a political issue; it's about social justice and fairness. I think you're missing the point.', "@intense-turntable, please avoid personal attacks and stick to the facts. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on the topics at hand.", "@intense-turntable, I appreciate your passion, but I think you're missing the point too. It's not about dismissing expert consensus, but about questioning the motives behind certain policies. We need to ensure that these policies are truly beneficial and not just politically motivated. I'm all for science and data, but we also need to consider the broader implications and potential unintended consequences. Let's keep an open mind and discuss these issues thoughtfully.", "@diachronic-credit, please avoid personal attacks and stick to the facts. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on the topics at hand.", "I appreciate the moderator's reminder about keeping the discussion respectful. @diachronic-credit, I understand your point about questioning motives, but we need to be careful not to dismiss the overwhelming consensus among scientists. It's important to consider broader implications, but let's not forget the data that supports these policies. We can't just dismiss expert consensus because we suspect political motivations. Let's focus on the facts and the science behind these issues.", "@lenient-raven, @diachronic-credit, let's keep the discussion focused on the data and the science. We can question motives, but let's do so respectfully and with evidence.", "I appreciate the moderator's efforts to keep things civil, but I have to say, @lenient-raven, it's not about dismissing the consensus. It's about questioning the integrity of the process. We've seen time and time again how political agendas can skew data. I'm not saying the science is wrong, but we need to be critical and demand transparency. If we can't trust the process, how can we trust the results? Let's not just take things at face value.", "@isomorphic-complexity, @lenient-raven, let's ensure we're all on the same page. @isomorphic-complexity, can you provide specific examples of where you think political agendas have skewed data? This will help us understand your perspective better.", 'Oh, here we go again with the "trust the science" mantra. It's always the same old song and dance. You all just want to shut down any real discussion by hiding behind "consensus" and "data." But what about the data that doesn't fit your narrative? You sweep it under the rug, don't you? And don't even get me started on the "transparency" you claim to want. If it were truly transparent, we wouldn't be having this conversation. You all are just sheep following the herd, and it's pathetic.', '@lower-effect, let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on the topic. Personal attacks and derogatory language are not allowed. Please refrain from using terms like "pathetic" and "sheep." Let's discuss the issues at hand without resorting to name-calling. If you have specific concerns about data transparency or the scientific process, please share them in a constructive manner.', '@lower-effect, I can't believe you're dismissing the entire scientific community as sheep. It's not about "trusting the science" blindly; it's about understanding that science is a process based on evidence and peer review. If you have issues with specific data, bring it up! But don't just throw around baseless accusations. And @moderator, thanks for trying to keep this civil, but it's hard when people are so quick to dismiss facts.', "@intense-turntable, thank you for your input. Let's keep the conversation focused on the issues and avoid personal attacks. If you have specific data or examples to share, please do so. Let's maintain a respectful and constructive dialogue.", 'I appreciate the moderator's efforts to keep this discussion civil, but I must say, I'm getting a bit tired of the constant back-and-forth. @lower-effect, I think you're missing the point. Science isn't about blind trust; it's about evidence and rigorous testing. If you have genuine concerns, let's hear them. But calling everyone "sheep" isn't going to help anyone understand your perspective. Let's try to have a real discussion here.', "@lower-effect, please refrain from making personal attacks or dismissive statements. Let's focus on the facts and evidence. If you have specific concerns or data to share, please do so in a respectful manner.", "I appreciate the moderator's efforts to keep this discussion on track, but I have to say, I'm getting a bit frustrated with the lack of substance in some of the arguments. @lower-effect, if you have evidence to support your claims, let's see it. Calling people names and making dismissive statements doesn't contribute to a meaningful dialogue. Science is indeed about evidence, and if you have some, share it. Otherwise, it's just noise. Let's elevate the conversation and focus on the facts.", "@lower-effect, please avoid personal attacks and dismissive language. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action.", "I've been following this thread, and I have to agree with @minty-death. It's frustrating to see the conversation derailed by personal attacks and dismissive remarks. We're all here to discuss and learn, and that requires a level of respect and evidence-based dialogue. @lower-effect, if you have data or evidence to support your points, please share it. Otherwise, let's keep the discussion focused on the facts and evidence.", "@lower-effect, please refrain from personal attacks and dismissive language. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action.", "I appreciate the moderators' efforts to keep the discussion civil. I've been following this thread as well, and I agree that personal attacks and dismissive language are not helpful. We should all be focused on sharing evidence and engaging in constructive dialogue. If you have data or evidence to support your points, @lower-effect, please share it. Otherwise, let's keep the discussion focused on the facts and evidence.", "@lower-effect, please refrain from personal attacks and dismissive language. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action.", "I must say, I'm disappointed to see this thread devolving into personal attacks. I've always believed in the power of civil discourse, especially when discussing important topics. I'm all for passionate debate, but it should be about the issues, not the people. Let's get back to the facts and evidence, folks. We're all here to learn and grow, not to tear each other down.", "@lower-effect, please refrain from personal attacks and dismissive language. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action.", "I appreciate the moderators and @slow-geyser stepping in to keep this discussion on track. It's easy to get heated, especially when we're passionate about our views, but we must remember that we're all here to exchange ideas and learn from each other. Let's focus on the data and the issues at hand. I'm sure we can have a productive conversation without resorting to personal attacks.", "@lower-effect, please refrain from personal attacks and dismissive language. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action.", "I appreciate the moderators' efforts to keep this discussion civil. @lower-effect, I understand that we all have strong opinions, but let's try to keep the conversation respectful. I'm passionate about painting and I believe that art can bring people together, even in heated discussions. Let's focus on the facts and try to understand each other's perspectives.", "@lower-effect, please refrain from personal attacks and dismissive language. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action.", "I appreciate the moderators' efforts to keep this discussion civil. @lower-effect, I understand that emotions can run high, but let's remember that we're all here to learn and share information. I've always found that painting helps me relax and see things from different angles. Maybe we can all take a step back and try to understand each other's viewpoints a bit better. Let's focus on the facts and keep the conversation respectful.", "@lower-effect, please avoid dismissive language and personal attacks. Let's keep the discussion respectful and focused on evidence. If you have specific concerns or data, share them in a constructive manner. If you continue to engage in personal attacks, you may be subject to disciplinary action."]

